</p>";s:14:"UF_SHOW_ON_OMS";s:1:"0";s:15:"~UF_SHOW_ON_OMS";s:1:"0";s:19:"UF_SHOW_ON_CONTACTS";s:1:"0";s:20:"~UF_SHOW_ON_CONTACTS";s:1:"0";s:15:"UF_ADM_POSITION";N;s:16:"~UF_ADM_POSITION";N;s:12:"UF_PHONE_EXT";N;s:13:"~UF_PHONE_EXT";N;s:14:"UF_NAME_DATIVE";s:52:"Сухомлиной Елене Николаевна";s:15:"~UF_NAME_DATIVE";s:52:"Сухомлиной Елене Николаевна";s:9:"UF_GENDER";N;s:10:"~UF_GENDER";N;s:13:"UF_PAGE_TITLE";s:106:"#FULL_NAME# — #SEO_SPECIALTY# в МЦРМ: запись на прием, отзывы пациентов";s:14:"~UF_PAGE_TITLE";s:106:"#FULL_NAME# — #SEO_SPECIALTY# в МЦРМ: запись на прием, отзывы пациентов";s:19:"UF_PAGE_DESCRIPTION";s:347:"Консультирует пациентов с нарушениями в системе гемостаза при планировании беременности, подготовке к ВРТ. Проводит наблюдения за пациентками во время беременности, в частности после ЭКО.";s:20:"~UF_PAGE_DESCRIPTION";s:347:"Консультирует пациентов с нарушениями в системе гемостаза при планировании беременности, подготовке к ВРТ. Проводит наблюдения за пациентками во время беременности, в частности после ЭКО.";s:16:"UF_PAGE_KEYWORDS";N;s:17:"~UF_PAGE_KEYWORDS";N;s:10:"UF_NAME_EN";s:9:"Dr. Elena";s:11:"~UF_NAME_EN";s:9:"Dr. Elena";s:17:"UF_SECOND_NAME_EN";N;s:18:"~UF_SECOND_NAME_EN";N;s:15:"UF_LAST_NAME_EN";s:10:"Sukhomlina";s:16:"~UF_LAST_NAME_EN";s:10:"Sukhomlina";s:19:"UF_WORK_POSITION_EN";s:38:"Hematologist, PhD, Associate Professor";s:20:"~UF_WORK_POSITION_EN";s:38:"Hematologist, PhD, Associate Professor";s:18:"UF_ADM_POSITION_EN";N;s:19:"~UF_ADM_POSITION_EN";N;s:12:"UF_DEGREE_EN";s:3:"PhD";s:13:"~UF_DEGREE_EN";s:3:"PhD";s:17:"UF_NAME_DATIVE_EN";N;s:18:"~UF_NAME_DATIVE_EN";N;s:16:"UF_PAGE_TITLE_EN";s:31:"#FULL_NAME# — #SEO_SPECIALTY#";s:17:"~UF_PAGE_TITLE_EN";s:31:"#FULL_NAME# — #SEO_SPECIALTY#";s:16:"UF_PAGE_DESCR_EN";N;s:17:"~UF_PAGE_DESCR_EN";N;s:19:"UF_PAGE_KEYWORDS_EN";N;s:20:"~UF_PAGE_KEYWORDS_EN";N;s:17:"UF_DESCRIPTION_EN";s:1604:"&lt;p&gt;
	 The main professional areas of Dr Elena Sukhomlina are: General Hematology (hemostasis disorders, thrombocytopenia, anemia of pregnancy).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 Dr. Sukhomlina consults family planning and pregnant patients with hemostasis disorders and during preparation for ART treatment cycles. Management of patients during pregnancy including those after IVF. Clinical immunohematology (Rh-incompatible pregnancy, haemolytic disease of the newborn).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 In her practice, Dr. Sukhomlina successfully uses her knowledge and skills as a hematologist, immunohematologist and transfusiologist which allows managing various patients in need of confirmation or ruling out hematologic diseases or diagnosis of Rh incompatibility in pregnancy.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 Author of more than 60 publications including textbooks and manuals for doctors in the sphere of hemostasis disorders.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 Dr. Sukhomlina is a regular participant of the Russian and international congresses such as 8th All-Russian Conference on &lt;span&gt;Clinical Hemostasiology and Hemorheology (2016), 3d World Congress &lt;em&gt;Controversies in Thrombosis and Hemostasis&lt;/em&gt; (CITH) (2016), the All-Russian Conference with International Participation &lt;em&gt;Hemostasis and Reproduction&lt;/em&gt; (2017). &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 She is an active participant of the National Association for Thrombosis and Hemostasis. Awarded with Certificate of Merit of the Russian Ministry of Health for her contribution into the national healthcare.
&lt;/p&gt;";s:18:"~UF_DESCRIPTION_EN";s:1496:"<p>
	 The main professional areas of Dr Elena Sukhomlina are: General Hematology (hemostasis disorders, thrombocytopenia, anemia of pregnancy).
</p>
<p>
	 Dr. Sukhomlina consults family planning and pregnant patients with hemostasis disorders and during preparation for ART treatment cycles. Management of patients during pregnancy including those after IVF. Clinical immunohematology (Rh-incompatible pregnancy, haemolytic disease of the newborn).
</p>
<p>
	 In her practice, Dr. Sukhomlina successfully uses her knowledge and skills as a hematologist, immunohematologist and transfusiologist which allows managing various patients in need of confirmation or ruling out hematologic diseases or diagnosis of Rh incompatibility in pregnancy.
</p>
<p>
	 Author of more than 60 publications including textbooks and manuals for doctors in the sphere of hemostasis disorders.
</p>
<p>
	 Dr. Sukhomlina is a regular participant of the Russian and international congresses such as 8th All-Russian Conference on <span>Clinical Hemostasiology and Hemorheology (2016), 3d World Congress <em>Controversies in Thrombosis and Hemostasis</em> (CITH) (2016), the All-Russian Conference with International Participation <em>Hemostasis and Reproduction</em> (2017). </span>
</p>
<p>
	 She is an active participant of the National Association for Thrombosis and Hemostasis. Awarded with Certificate of Merit of the Russian Ministry of Health for her contribution into the national healthcare.
